ss=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3614289\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 15, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lbe1677053515050.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lbe1677053515050.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lbe1677053515050.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lbe1677053515050\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The following procedure allows developers to enable or disable Uniface debugger\n\t\tbreakpoints based on the defined errors or exceptions break-on conditions on the\n\t\t\t<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Settings</span> &gt; <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Error</span> configuration tab. </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lbe1677053515050__step_w1920ab1b5b1b1_w1921ab1b5b1_w1922ab1b5_w1923ab1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">On the <span class=\"keyword wintitle\">Uniface Debugger</span> window, navigate to\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">View</span> &gt; <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Settings</span>.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup stepresult\">The system displays the <span class=\"keyword wintitle\">Settings</span> dialog\n\t\t\t\t\tbox.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lbe1677053515050__step_w1924ab1b5b1b3_w1925ab1b5b1_w1926ab1b5_w1927ab1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Errors</span> tab.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup stepresult\">The system displays the <span class=\"keyword wintitle\">Errors</span> screen.<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"lbe1677053515050__fig_kdq_pyg_pwb\">\n<img alt=\"Specific Error screen\" class=\"image\" id=\"lbe1677053515050__image_cjb_ssr_qwb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/Specific-Error-screen.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure></div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lbe1677053515050__step_w1928ab1b5b1b5_w1929ab1b5b1_w1930ab1b5_w1931ab1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Select any of the following required conditions:</span>\n<ul class=\"ul choices\" id=\"lbe1677053515050__choices_atq_dxg_pwb\">\n<li class=\"li choice\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Do not break</span>: Use this option to disable debugger breaks on any\n\t\t\t\t\t\terror or exception, irrespective of the specific Proc error codes defined\n\t\t\t\t\t\tunder the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Specific errors</span> radio option.</li>\n<li class=\"li choice\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">All errors regarded as exceptions</span>: Use this option to enable\n\t\t\t\t\t\tdebugger breaks on all errors that occur in exception-enabled code,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tirrespective of the specific Proc error codes defined under the\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Specific errors</span> radio option.</li>\n<li class=\"li choice\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">All errors</span>: Use this option to enable debugger breaks on all\n\t\t\t\t\t\terrors, irrespective of the specific Proc error codes defined under the\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Specific errors</span> radio option.</li>\n<li class=\"li choice\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Specific errors</span>: Use this option to enable debugger breaks on\n\t\t\t\t\t\tthe Proc error codes defined under this option. When you select this option,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tyou must add or remove error numbers as per the requirement.</li>\n</ul>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lbe1677053515050__step_w1932ab1b5b1b7_w1933ab1b5b1_w1934ab1b5_w1935ab1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Apply</span> to activate the new configuration\n\t\t\t\t\tchanges.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup stepresult\">You can now compile your codes and test your settings.</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614289\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614289\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Configuring the Debugger Error and Exception behavior Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 15, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The following procedure allows developers to enable or disable Uniface debugger breakpoints based on the defined errors or exceptions break-on conditions on the Settings > Error configuration tab. On the Uniface Debugger window, navigate to View > Settings . The system displays the Settings dialog box. Click the Errors tab. The system displays the Errors screen. Select any of the following required conditions: Do not break : Use this option to disable debugger breaks on any error or exception, irrespective of the specific Proc error codes defined under the Specific errors radio option. All errors regarded as exceptions : Use this option to enable debugger breaks on all errors that occur in exception-enabled code, irrespective of the specific Proc error codes defined under the Specific errors radio option. All errors : Use this option to enable debugger breaks on all errors, irrespective of the specific Proc error codes defined under the Specific errors radio option. Specific errors : Use this option to enable debugger breaks on the Proc error codes defined under this option. When you select this option, you must add or remove error numbers as per the requirement. Click Apply to activate the new configuration changes. You can now compile your codes and test your settings. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}